Senator Daniel
1 moves to amend the bill on page 17, lines 25–26, by inserting the following between the lines:
2 "MODIFY LAW GOVERNING LITIGATION COSTS UNDER G.S. 42-46
3 SECTION 11.8.(a) G.S. 42-46(i) reads as rewritten:
4 "(i) Out-of-Pocket Expenses and Litigation Costs. – In addition to the late fees referenced
5 in subsections (a) and (b) of this section and the administrative fees of a landlord referenced in
6 subsections (e) through (g) of this section, a landlord also is permitted to charge and recover from
7 a tenant the following actual out-of-pocket expenses:
8 …
9 (3) If the landlord is the prevailing party, reasonableReasonable attorneys' fees
10 actually paid or owed, pursuant to a written lease, not to exceed fifteen percent
11 (15%) of the amount owed by the tenant, or fifteen percent (15%) of the
12 monthly rent stated in the lease if the eviction is based on a default other than
13 the nonpayment of rent. In cases where a tenant appeals a summary ejectment
14 to district court, a landlord is entitled to an award of all actual reasonable
15 attorneys' fees paid or owed if a court determines that the tenant knew, or
16 should have known, the appeal was frivolous, unreasonable, without
17 foundation, or in bad faith or solely for the purpose of delay
18 (4) In cases where a tenant appeals a summary ejectment to district court, if the
19 landlord is the prevailing party, a landlord is entitled to an award of all actual
20 reasonable attorneys' fees paid or owed if a court determines that the tenant
21 knew, or should have known, the appeal was frivolous, unreasonable, without
22 foundation, or in bad faith or solely for the purpose of delay."
23 SECTION 11.8.(b) This section is effective retroactively to September 9, 2024.".
*S648-ACN-16-v-2*

